text: {| |} The Savoia-Marchetti S.84 was an Italian twin-engined airliner developed, in Italy, from the three-engined Savoia-Marchetti S.73; only the prototype was completed and the designation was re-used for the Savoia- Marchetti SM.84 ==Specifications (S.84 prototype) == ==Notes== ==References== * Category:1930s Italian airliners Category:World War II Italian transport aircraft S.84 Category:Low-wing aircraft Category:Twin piston-engined tractor aircraft Category:Aircraft first flown in 1936
